    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 195.91/740</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SRP1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 10.<note n="1" xml:id="d136fn1">Not printed.</note> Merchandise
                    from United States to war zone in Allied sailing vessels is prohibited, and
                    every effort is being made to restrict neutral sailing vessels going through war
                        zone.<note n="2" xml:id="d136fn2">See resolution of Exports Administrative
                        Board, Sept. 19, as amended Oct. 4, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_957">p. 957</ref>.</note> So far only permissions given have
                    been for neutral vessel charters made before our restrictions went into
                    effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
